<font color="#FF0000">WHAT ARE THE GOOD CHOICES?</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jul 29 17:17:44 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Something that was hard for me to watch was how these strong and insightful young women had to compromise their aspirations about who they wanted to be, just to survive growing up. I think teenagers and young women can have meaningful dreams but how can we make choices that reflect what we want -what we want for ourselves- without giving in to the pressures of the world? But how do we know if what we want is not already a compromise? 
